@node "Document_1" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub} 

Cal V1.1 is a simple calendar utility which displays a calendar in the
Shell/Cli window for any month from January 1978 to December 2077.

There are no special requirements to use Cal.  It should even run on WB 1.3
(not tested) although I don't know if there's anyone out there using it.

I hope you find it useful.
@endnode

@node "Document_2" "Installation"
@{b}Installation@{ub}

There are no special installation instructions for Cal.  Copy Cal to the
directory of your choice; preferably in the command path - such as your c
directory.
@endnode

@node "Document_3" "Usage"
@{b}Usage@{ub}

Command format: 'cal [mmmyy][?]'

Options: [mmmyy] -      month & year to display that calendar
                        ie. 'jan96' or 'SEP99 - case insensitive'
                        (only valid from January 1978 - December 2077)

         [?]     -      Displays this HELP message

Entering 'cal' without arguments displays the calendar for the current month
@endnode

